# Build context = repository root (the Dockerfile needs go.work + DataPlane/).
# Keep the context tiny: smaller upload, faster builds, and — critically — no
# secrets or runtime data can ever leak into an image layer.

# ── VCS / CI / docs (never needed to compile the binaries) ───────────────────
.git
.gitattributes
.github
.gitignore
docs
*.md

# ── Infrastructure & tooling (not part of the app image) ─────────────────────
infra
scripts
Makefile
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore
**/Dockerfile

# ── Editor / OS noise ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode
.idea
*.iml
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Go build / test artifacts & local caches ─────────────────────────────────
bin
dist
build
out
vendor
**/*.test
**/*.out
**/*.exe
**/*.exe~
**/*.prof
**/*.pprof
coverage.*
go.work.sum
# Test sources are not needed to build the two binaries; exclude to shrink ctx.
**/*_test.go

# ── Runtime data — the WAL must NEVER be baked into an image ──────────────────
data
**/*.wal
**/*.rdb
**/*.aof

# ── Secrets — defense in depth; these must never enter a layer ────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
secrets
